{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06b49160-d608-4a55-a12d-f027522a6c29","content":"\n\nFor a **Web API project**, common templates and auth options depend on your stack:\n\n### .NET\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity-based (JWT bearer tokens)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n### Node.js\n- **Express** + `passport.js` (JWT, OAuth2, local)\n- **Fastify** + `@fastify/jwt`\n- **NestJS** with built-in Guards (JWT, OAuth2, API keys)\n\n### Python\n- **FastAPI** + `python-jose` (JWT) or OAuth2 flows\n- **Django REST Framework** + `djangorestframework-simplejwt`\n\n### Common auth approaches\n| Method | Best for |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth2 / OIDC** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **API Keys** | Server-to-server |\n| **Cookie-based** | Traditional web apps |\n\nWhich stack are you targeting? I can scaffold a project for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c20244e7-677e-4c44-b842-2b14126d3741","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":352},"id":"899df8ff-9419-4372-b18a-dbe020229c07","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:45:35.591Z","parentId":"693b9493-423c-4690-8070-e220e698949d"}
